text: Dhanuha is a census town in Jaunpur district in the state of Uttar Pradesh, India. ==Demographics== India census, Dhanauha had a population of 6,213. Males constitute 53% of the population and females 47%. Dhanauha has an average literacy rate of 58%, lower than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 69% and, female literacy is 46%. In Dhanauha, 17% of the population is under 6 years of age. ==References== Category:Cities and towns in Jaunpur district
title: Dhanauha
